TY  - JOUR
T1  - Modelling Emergency Lateral Transshipments in Inventory Systems
AU  - Axsäter, Sven
Y1  - 1990/11/01
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/11/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.36.11.1329
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.36.11.1329
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1329
EP  - 1338
VL  - 36
IS  - 11
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In inventory systems with several bases that support different geographical regions, it is quite common to allow emergency lateral transshipments between the bases. This may be advantageous if neighbouring bases are at shorter distances than the central depot or the external supplier. This paper provides a new technique for modelling such lateral transshipments in continuous review inventory systems with one-for-one replenishments and Poisson demand. We apply this technique to a two-echelon system with repairable items.
AB  - In inventory systems with several bases that support different geographical regions, it is quite common to allow emergency lateral transshipments between the bases. This may be advantageous if neighbouring bases are at shorter distances than the central depot or the external supplier. This paper provides a new technique for modelling such lateral transshipments in continuous review inventory systems with one-for-one replenishments and Poisson demand. We apply this technique to a two-echelon system with repairable items.
